shared_text:
Wharton County Youth Fair
July 3 at 9:27 AM ·

In light of Gov. Abbott’s proclamation issued Thursday, July 2 requiring face masks to be worn in public and limiting gatherings to no more than 10 people, the Executive Board voted to cancel the livestock shows and pageants scheduled for July 10 and 11. Fair President Rodney Jedlicka said a decision will be made at a later date regarding rescheduling of any of these events. Once again we are very sorry we were forced to make this difficult decision.
Continued prayers for everyone's health and safety! God bless you all!

The East Bernard FFA Booster Club will be sponsoring their annual Bake Sale Fundraiser on Saturday, October 12, 2019 at the corner of HWY 60 & 90A from 8am til approx 11am.

We ask that FFA members and Booster Club members provide 1-2 baked items to sell. Baked goods may be dropped off at the AG Shop by 3:15 on Friday, or bring to the sale on Saturday morning.

We are also needing volunteers to work that morning. Kids will be able to count hours worked towards community service hours.

EB FFA Booster Club NOVEMBER MEETING

post_text:
1st Annual EB FFA Family Night & Meeting
The EB FFA will have its first meeting of the year on Monday September 23rd at the school cafeteria.
The evening will begin with a Pot Luck Dinner at 6:30 pm. Please bring a dish to share.
The FFA will provide drinks and paper goods.
The official FFA meeting will begin at 7 pm.
There will be an EB FFA Booster Club meeting immediately following the FFA meeting.
